[{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"CurrentModule = NamedRowArrays","category":"page"},{"location":"#NamedRowArrays","page":"Home","title":"NamedRowArrays","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"NamedRowArrays provides an array type that knows about its row names. This allows for indexing by name in a straightforward manner in addition to the regular indexing possibilities.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Modules = [NamedRowArrays]","category":"page"},{"location":"#NamedRowArrays.NamedRowArray","page":"Home","title":"NamedRowArrays.NamedRowArray","text":"A NamedRowArray is an AbstractArray that wraps another AbstractArray (only AbstractVector and AbstractMatrix, however) and adds row names to the first array dimension. AxisArrays can be indexed by using the named rows as an alternative to positional indexing by dimension.\n\nType parameters\n\nThe NamedRowArray contains several type parameters:\n\nstruct AxisArray{T,N,D,R} <: AbstractArray{T,N}\n\nT : the elemental type of the AbstractArray\nN : the number of dimensions\nD : the type of the wrapped AbstractArray\nR : the names of the rows, as a NTuple{N, Symbol}\n\nConstructors\n\nWhen constructing a NamedRowArray, note that no copy of the array is made.\n\nNamedRowArray(A::AbstractArray, rownames::Tuple)\nNamedRowArray(A::AbstractArray, rownames::AbstractVector)\n\nIndexing\n\nNamedRowArrays can be indexed in the same way as normal AbstractArrays. In addition, one can also use the rownames instead of the numerical indices. Since only the rows can have names, it is also possible to obtain one or more rows of a Matrix by only passing one or more row names as the index.\n\nExamples\n\nFor a Vector:\n\nv = NamedRowArray(rand(3), [:a, :b, :c])\nv[1] # scalar value\nv[:a] # scalar value\nv[2:3] # 2-element NamedRowVector\nv[[:a, :b]] # 2-element NamedRowVector\n\nFor a Matrix:\n\na = NamedRowArray(rand(3, 10), [:a, :b, :c])\na[1, 3] # scalar value\na[:a, 3] # scalar value\na[:a, 2:3] # 2-element Vector\na[:a] # whole row: 10-element Vector\na[[:a, :b]] # two rows: 2×10 NamedRowMatrix\na[:, 3] # one column: 3-element NamedRowVector\na[:, 2:3] # two columns: 3×2 NamedRowMatrix\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#NamedRowArrays.NamedRowMatrix","page":"Home","title":"NamedRowArrays.NamedRowMatrix","text":"NamedRowMatrix{T,D,R}\n\nAlias for NamedRowArray{T,2,D,R}.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#NamedRowArrays.NamedRowVector","page":"Home","title":"NamedRowArrays.NamedRowVector","text":"NamedRowVector{T,D,R}\n\nAlias for NamedRowArray{T,1,D,R}.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"}]
